		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To emulate the palette of an NTSC or PAL NES, see <a href="http://nesdevwiki.ath.cx/index.php/NTSC_Video" class="postlink">NTSC Video</a>. The formulas are the same for NTSC and PAL, but the PAL NES uses a fixed phase offset of -15, while the NTSC phase offset can vary from -45 to +45 depending on how the TV's tint dial is set.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


